      <section eId="sec_CCP-3994">
        <num>CCP 3994</num>
        <heading>3994. Â Emancipation hearing</heading>
        <subsection eId="CCP-3994__subsec_A">
          <num>A.</num>
          <content>
            <p>An emancipation hearing shall be a summary proceeding.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCP-3994__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>Except for good cause shown, the minor shall be present at the hearing and may be called as a witness by the court.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCP-3994__subsec_C">
          <num>C.</num>
          <content>
            <p>With the consent of all parties and the court, judicial emancipation may be granted without a hearing upon a joint petition for emancipation.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=111898</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
